  "prompt": "My girlfriend and I took a break. About two months later she told me she made out with her ex during our break. What do I do?",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're going through this. Discovering that your girlfriend was involved with someone else during your break can be hurtful and confusing. Here are a few steps you might consider to help navigate this situation:\n\n1. **Take Time to Process Your Emotions:**\n   - Allow yourself to feel whatever emotions arise\u2014whether it's hurt, anger, confusion, or sadness. It's important to acknowledge and understand your feelings before making any decisions.\n\n2. **Reflect on Your Relationship:**\n   - Think about the reasons you took the break in the first place. Consider whether the relationship is meeting your needs and if you're both willing to work through challenges together.\n\n3. **Communicate Openly:**\n   - Have an honest and calm conversation with your girlfriend. Share how her actions made you feel and listen to her perspective. Understanding each other's viewpoints can provide clarity on the next steps.\n\n4. **Assess Trust and Commitment:**\n   - Trust is a fundamental part of any relationship. Consider whether you can rebuild trust and if both of you are committed to moving forward together.\n\n5. **Seek Support:**\n   - Talking to close friends, family members, or a professional counselor can provide you with additional support and guidance during this time.\n\n6. **Decide What's Best for You:**\n   - Ultimately, prioritize your well-being. Whether you choose to work on the relationship or move on, make sure it's a decision that aligns with your values and happiness.\n\nRemember, relationships are complex, and it's okay to seek help in making decisions that are right for you. Take care of yourself during this challenging time.",
